==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mosasauria
<hw>Mos`a*sau"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Mosasaurus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An order of
large, extinct, marine reptiles, found in the Cretaceous rocks,
especially in America. They were serpentlike in form and in having
loosely articulated and dilatable jaws, with large recurved teeth, but
they had paddlelike feet. Some of them were over fifty feet long. They
are, essentially, fossil sea serpents with paddles. Called also
<altname>Pythonomarpha</altname>, and
<altname>Mosasauria</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mosasaurus</ent>⟦br⟧
